                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1071a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-31T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Minister of Ecuador at Washington, in informal conversation stated that daily
                    quotas for payment of interest on railway bonds would be resumed without delay.
                    Inform Department whether such payments are being made and if not, when they
                    will begin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
